trend_summary: Core grid remained largely intact, with only scattered infill and rooftop redevelopments. River-edge parks were progressively landscaped, trails and pedestrian bridges added, and tree canopy expanded. Waterfront sediment and water levels varied through years but no major land reclamation occurred. Overall pattern stayed compact and built-up, with modest green and public-realm upgrades.
notable_changes: Incremental replacement of a few low-rise roofs by larger, modern rooftops indicating infill redevelopment.
Addition of new paved trails and small footbridges along the riverfront park system.
Expansion and thickening of tree canopy in parks and along several streets.
Reconfiguration of some highway on-ramps and roundabouts, improving circulation.
Seasonal or year-to-year shifts in river turbidity and sandbars, but no permanent shoreline change.
